Note:
==============================================================================
palette - CSS Named Colors, Palette Generation, WCAG Contrast
==============================================================================

This module provides:

  - The 147 standard named colours defined by W3C CSS Color Module
    Level 4 (red, blue, mistyrose, rebeccapurple, ...) as Float64 RGB
    triples in non-linear sRGB [0, 1]. The full list matches
    https://www.w3.org/TR/css-color-4/#named-colors verbatim.

  - palette_lookup_by_name(name_ptr, out_rgb) -> Integer
  - palette_lookup(qualified_name, out_rgb) -> Integer  (namespace
    prefix dispatch covering all 192 names across css/, material/,
    tailwind/, x11/ families)
  - palette_nearest_named(rgb) -> name string (matched by Oklab distance)
  - generate_palette_* family: evenly-spaced, monochromatic,
    complementary, triadic, tetradic, analogous palettes via OKLCh
    hue rotation.
  - material_design_swatch_500: the canonical Material Design 2014
    500-shade lookup by hue name (red, pink, purple, deep-purple,
    indigo, blue, light-blue, cyan, teal, green, light-green, lime,
    yellow, amber, orange, deep-orange, brown, grey, blue-grey).
  - tailwind_swatch_500: Tailwind CSS 3.x 500-shade lookup (slate,
    gray, zinc, neutral, stone, red, orange, amber, yellow, lime,
    green, emerald, teal, cyan, sky, blue, indigo, violet, purple,
    fuchsia, pink, rose).
  - x11_named_lookup: X11 rgb.txt extras (grey variants not in CSS).
  - WCAG 2.1 contrast_ratio + AA/AAA threshold checks.

References:
  - W3C CSS Color Module Level 4 (CSS-COLOR-4) Section "Named Colors"
  - WCAG 2.1 Section 1.4.3 (Contrast (Minimum))
  - Material Design 2014 colour palette specification
==============================================================================
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/arithmetic_core.runa" as Arith
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StrCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/color/oklab.runa" as Oklab
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPES
Note: ============================================================================

Type called "NamedColorEntry":
    name as String
    r as Float
    g as Float
    b as Float
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: NAMED COLOR ACCESSORS (CSS Color Module Level 4)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "named_color_count" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Total number of CSS-named colours exposed by this module.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Returns the literal 147.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single load.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Return 147
End Process

Process called "named_color_at" takes index as Integer returns NamedColorEntry:
    @Reasoning
    Return the (name, r, g, b) tuple for the colour at the given index.
    Index 0 is "aliceblue"; index 146 is "yellowgreen". For
    out-of-range index returns a zero-named entry.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Linear dispatch via If-chain. Each branch contains the CSS spec value
    encoded as Float triples (the 8-bit canonical CSS values divided by
    255 at construction time).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(index) average; primarily called via palette_lookup_by_name which
    short-circuits on name match.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let entry be a value of type NamedColorEntry
    Set entry.name to ""
    Set entry.r to 0.0
    Set entry.g to 0.0
    Set entry.b to 0.0
    If index is equal to 0:
        Set entry.name to "aliceblue"
        Set entry.r to 0.9411764705882353
        Set entry.g to 0.9725490196078431
        Set entry.b to 1.0
    End If
